Below is the **complete system-level architecture and governance model** for:

# üî∑ LOGIC 10 ‚Äì Award Decision & Contract Formation Logic

This logic converts evaluation outcomes into **legally enforceable contracts** while preserving transparency, auditability, and procedural integrity.

It is the bridge between:

* Evaluation Framework (Logic 8)
* Price Intelligence (Logic 9)
* Contract Execution & Performance Management (Logic 11 ‚Äì future stage)

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ PURPOSE OF LOGIC 10

This logic ensures:

* Awards strictly follow pre-defined evaluation rules
* No post-evaluation manipulation
* Proper internal approval before award
* Transparent communication to bidders
* Legal contract formation
* Audit trail for governance

It protects the organization from:

* Bid protests
* Corruption claims
* Policy violations
* Unauthorized award decisions
* Legal disputes

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ HIGH-LEVEL FLOW

```
Evaluation Completed (Logic 8)
        ‚Üì
Score Validation Check
        ‚Üì
Award Recommendation Generated
        ‚Üì
Compliance & Governance Review
        ‚Üì
Approval Workflow
        ‚Üì
Award Decision Locked
        ‚Üì
Award Notification Issued
        ‚Üì
Standstill Period (if applicable)
        ‚Üì
Contract Draft Generation
        ‚Üì
Digital Signing
        ‚Üì
Contract Activation
        ‚Üì
Transition to Execution
```

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ AWARD DECISION CONTROL LOGIC

---

## üîπ A. Rule Consistency Enforcement

System verifies:

* Winning bid has highest final score (or lowest evaluated cost)
* All mandatory requirements met
* No unresolved risk flags (Logic 9)
* Evaluation panel completed scoring properly
* No unauthorized scoring changes

If deviation occurs:

```
System blocks award ‚Üí Escalation required
```

---

## üîπ B. Tie-Breaker Logic

Pre-configured rules such as:

* Higher technical score prevails
* Local SME preference
* Lower lifecycle cost
* Earlier submission timestamp

Tie-breaker must be pre-defined in Logic 3 and cannot be changed post-bid opening.

---

## üîπ C. Disqualification Confirmation

Before award:

System re-checks:

* Compliance documents validity
* Financial capacity thresholds
* Conflict-of-interest declarations
* Sanctions screening
* Blacklist status

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ APPROVAL WORKFLOW STRUCTURE

Award must pass internal governance levels based on:

| Contract Value | Required Approval   |
| -------------- | ------------------- |
| Low            | Procurement Officer |
| Medium         | Department Head     |
| High           | Executive Committee |
| Strategic      | Board / Ministerial |

System enforces:

* Sequential approval
* Digital signature logging
* No bypassing workflow

All decisions time-stamped.

---

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ AWARD NOTIFICATION LOGIC

Once approved:

---

## üîπ A. Winning Supplier Notification

Includes:

* Final evaluated price
* Contract summary
* Acceptance deadline
* Required documentation
* Performance security requirement (if applicable)

---

## üîπ B. Unsuccessful Bidder Notification

Includes:

* Notification of non-selection
* Summary of evaluation outcome
* Their score (if policy allows)
* Appeal process instructions
* Standstill period duration

Supports transparency and dispute mitigation.

---

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ STANDSTILL PERIOD (FOR PUBLIC PROCUREMENT)

Optional but critical in regulated systems.

Purpose:

* Allow unsuccessful bidders to challenge award
* Prevent immediate contract signing

Flow:

```
Award Announced
‚Üì
Standstill Countdown (e.g., 10 days)
‚Üì
If No Formal Challenge ‚Üí Proceed
If Challenge Filed ‚Üí Suspend Contract Formation
```

---

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ CONTRACT GENERATION LOGIC

---

## üîπ A. Automated Contract Drafting

System pulls:

* Tender specifications (Logic 3)
* Winning bid details (Logic 6)
* Negotiated clarifications (if allowed)
* Standard contract template
* Applicable legal jurisdiction
* Pricing structure

Auto-generates structured contract document.

---

## üîπ B. Contract Types Supported

* Fixed-price contract
* Framework agreement
* Unit-rate contract
* Milestone-based payment contract
* Service-level agreement (SLA)
* Call-off contract under framework

---

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ CONTRACT VALIDATION CHECKS

Before signing:

* Contract matches tender terms (no material deviation)
* Price matches awarded amount
* Scope unchanged
* Delivery schedule consistent
* Performance guarantees included
* Insurance requirements validated

System blocks modification of material conditions post-award unless formally justified.

---

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ DIGITAL SIGNATURE & LEGAL FORMATION

---

## üîπ A. Signature Workflow

```
Buyer Authorized Signatory
‚Üì
Supplier Authorized Signatory
‚Üì
Contract Locked
```

Features:

* Multi-factor authentication
* Time-stamped signing
* IP logging
* Document hash fingerprint
* Version freeze after signing

---

## üîπ B. Contract Activation

Triggered when:

* Both parties sign
* Required securities submitted
* Insurance verified
* Standstill period expired (if applicable)

System status changes to:

```
ACTIVE CONTRACT
```

---

# üîü PERFORMANCE SECURITY & GUARANTEES

If required:

* Bank guarantee upload
* Performance bond validation
* Retention clause activation
* Insurance certificate verification

System validates:

* Validity period
* Amount threshold
* Issuing institution authenticity

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ POST-AWARD DATA LOCKING

After award:

* Evaluation data frozen
* Scores immutable
* Justifications archived
* Price intelligence snapshot stored
* Audit trail sealed

Prevents retroactive manipulation.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ APPEAL & DISPUTE HANDLING LOGIC

If bidder challenges:

System logs:

* Date of complaint
* Nature of challenge
* Evidence attached
* Review committee assignment
* Resolution outcome

Possible outcomes:

* Award upheld
* Re-evaluation ordered
* Tender canceled
* Disciplinary investigation initiated

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ FRAMEWORK AGREEMENT LOGIC (ADVANCED)

If multiple winners:

* Ranked supplier list created
* Mini-competition logic defined
* Call-off rules pre-configured
* Allocation model (rotation / best-price / hybrid)

Supports long-term multi-supplier arrangements.

---

