---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ SECURITY & GOVERNANCE CONTROLS

* Separation of duties (RBAC ‚Äì Logic 2)
* Award lock after approval
* Immutable audit logs
* Conflict-of-interest reconfirmation
* Independent compliance verification
* No editing contract after signature
* Version-controlled templates

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ RISK MITIGATION FEATURES

Prevents:

* Award to non-highest scorer
* Post-bid negotiation manipulation (unless allowed by procedure)
* Contract scope expansion without approval
* Undocumented price changes
* Ghost approvals
* Fake contract signatories

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ KEY PERFORMANCE METRICS

* Award cycle time
* Number of challenged awards
* Appeal success rate
* Contract amendment frequency
* Post-award disputes
* Average approval duration
* Contract signing delay rate

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ COMMON FAILURE POINTS (TO DESIGN AGAINST)

‚ùå Award deviates from scoring logic
‚ùå Manual override without record
‚ùå Contract terms differ from tender
‚ùå Missing performance guarantees
‚ùå No standstill mechanism
‚ùå Delayed notification to bidders
‚ùå Unclear appeal path

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ STRATEGIC IMPACT

Logic 10:

* Converts evaluation into enforceable outcome
* Protects organization legally
* Strengthens supplier trust
* Reduces corruption risk
* Enables downstream performance management
* Creates institutional accountability

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£0Ô∏è‚É£ SYSTEM-WIDE ROLE IN ECOSYSTEM

Logic 10 connects:

* Logic 1 (Identity & Trust) ‚Üí validated signatories
* Logic 2 (RBAC) ‚Üí approval authority
* Logic 3 (Need Definition) ‚Üí scope integrity
* Logic 6 (Bid Submission) ‚Üí locked bid content
* Logic 8 (Evaluation) ‚Üí scoring output
* Logic 9 (Price Intelligence) ‚Üí risk validation

It marks the transition from:

**Competition Phase ‚Üí Contractual Obligation Phase**

